b insurgency]]\n|-\n|August 6 \n|[[Explosive device]] \n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:right\"|2\n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:right\"|1\n|Vitoria, [[Spain]] \n|Two policemen were killed and a woman slightly injured when an explosive device consisting of 10kg of amonal and abundant shrapnel exploded as two police cars passed <ref>https://elpais.com/diario/1987/08/07/espana/555285608_850215.html</ref> \n|[[ETA (separatist group)|ETA]] \n|[[Basque Conflict]] \n|-\n|August 10 \n|[[Car bombing]] \n|style=\"background:#E0FFFF;text-align:right\"|0\n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:right\"|14\n|\u00c9ibar,[[Spain]] \n|14 people were slightly injured when a car bomb exploded in Eibar. \n|[[ETA (separatist group)|ETA]] \n|[[Basque Conflict]] \n|-\n|August 18\n|[[1987 grenade attack in the Sri Lankan Parliament|Grenades]]\n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:right\"|2\n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:right\"|16\n|[[Sri Jayawardenepura Kotte]], [[Sri Lanka]]\n|A member of the banned [[communist]] party [[Janatha Vimukthi Peramuna]] (People's Liberation Front) threw two hand grenades into the [[Parliament of Sri Lanka]], narrowly missing president [[J. R. Jayewardene]] and prime minister [[Ranasinghe Premadasa]] and killing an MP and a Ministry secretary.\n|[[Janatha Vimukthi Peramuna]]\n|[[1987\u201389 JVP insurrection|JVP insurgency]] \n|-\n|September 8 \n|[[Assassination]] \n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:right\"|1\n|style=\"background:#E0FFFF;text-align:right\"|0\n|Bilbao,[[Spain]]\n|The second lieutenant of the Civil Guard, Crist\u00f3bal Martin Luengo, was killed by a shot to the neck by members of ETA <ref>https://elpais.com/diario/1987/09/09/espana/558136807_850215.html</ref> \n|[[ETA (separatist group)|ETA]]\n|[[Basque Conflict]]\n|-\n|September 10 \n|[[Homemade explosive]] \n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:right\"|1\n|style=\"background:#E0FFFF;text-align:right\"|0 \n|Borjas Blancas, [[Spain]] \n|Bomb attack against the Court in Borjas Blancas. As a result of the terrorist attack dies Emilia Aldom\u00e0 i Sans.\n|[[Terra Lliure]] \n|[[Terrorism in Spain]] \n|-\n|October 30\n|Roadside Bombing\n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:right\"|10\n|Unknown\n|[[Tame, Arauca]], [[Colombia]]\n|Guerrillas of the [[National Liberation Army (Colombia)|ELN]] Domingo Lain Front, dynamite a vehicle of the National Police, in the area of Betoyes, jurisdiction of Tame (Arauca). Captain Jose Ignacio Ayala and 9 agents are killed.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=N2osnxbUuuUC&dat=19871101&printsec=frontpage&hl=es | title=El Tiempo - B\u00fasqueda en el archivo de Google Noticias}}</ref>\n|[[National Liberation Army (Colombia)|ELN]]\n|[[Colombian conflict]]\n|-\n|October 31\n|Assassination,Shooting\n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:right\"|8\n|style=\"background:#E0FFFF;text-align:right\"|0\n|[[Cundinamarca Department]], [[Colombia]]\n|In Bejucales Veracruz of Yacopi (Cundinamarca), guerrillas of the 22nd Front of the FARC, murdered 8 peasants accused of collaborating with the Public Force.<ref>http://cundinet.cundinamarca.gov.co:8080/aplicaciones/gobernacion/centroDocumental/doc-secgenofvic.nsf/0/626E6C20B6F9211A05257D5B0077ABFE/$FILE/Plan%20integral%20prevenci%C3%B3n%20Yacop%C3%AD%2019-09-2013-%20YACOPI.pdf</ref>\n|[[FARC]] [[militants]]\n|[[Colombian conflict]]\n|-\n|November 1 \n|[[Assasination]] \n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:right\"|1\n|style=\"background:#E0FFFF;text-align:right\"|0\n|Ordizia, [[Spain]] \n|A corporal of the Civil Guard was killed by several shots to the head by members of ETA in Ordizia. <ref>https://elpais.com/diario/1987/11/02/espana/562806006_850215.html</ref> \n|[[ETA (separatist group)|ETA]] \n|[[Basque conflict]] \n|-\n|November 8\n|[[Remembrance Day bombing|Bombing]]\n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:right\"|12\n|style=\"background:#FEDB81;text-align:right\"|63\n|[[Enniskillen]], [[Northern Ireland]]\n|[[Provisional IRA|